<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1708" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1708">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 850d.00/258c.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 370.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence with
                            your Legation regarding the approaching International Conference on
                            Spitzbergen which is to be held at Christiania on or about June 16,
                            1914, I have the honor to advise you of the appointment by this
                            Government of Mr. William Miller Collier of Auburn, New York, and Mr.
                            Albert G. Schmedeman, Envoy Extraordinary and Minister Plenipotentiary
                            of the United States at Christiania, as delegates to represent the
                            Government of the United States at that International Conference.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>